We've got to split before the police get here.
我们得在警察来之前离开。

142
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:10,480
Example two.
例子二。

143
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:11,880
This party is boring.
这个派对很无聊。

144
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:17,160
Let's split.
我们走吧。

145
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:20,720
Example three.
例子三。

146
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:24,400
I have to wake up early tomorrow, so we're going to split.
我明天要早起，所以我们得走了。

147
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:25,800
Okay.
好的。

148
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:26,800
Very good.
很好。

149
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,800
So split.
所以“split”。

150
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,960
Now also, I think you can use it for relationships, right?
另外，我觉得你也可以用在关系上，对吧？

151
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:32,960
Me and him, me and her split up.
我和他，我和她分手了。

152
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:33,960
That's right.
没错。

153
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:34,960
So you ended your relationship.
所以你们结束了关系。

154
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:35,960
Yeah.
是的。

155
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:36,960
Split.
分手。

156
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:37,960
Okay.
好的。

157
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:42,240
So we saw five really common phrases from the 1960s.
所以我们看到了五个60年代非常常见的短语。

158
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:46,480
Let's listen to the dialogue again a little bit slower, and then we'll come back and look
让我们再听一遍对话，慢一点，然后回来看看60年代的一些短语。

159
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:53,320
at some phrases from the 60s.
60年代的短语。

160
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:55,360
Hey man, I really like your pad.
嘿，老兄，我真的很喜欢你的公寓。

161
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:57,680
Those lava lamps are far out.
那些熔岩灯太酷了。

162
