194
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:10,240
And when he says, I dig it, he says, I understand.
当他说“我明白”时，他说我理解。

195
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:11,240
Yeah.
是的。

196
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,240
Okay.
好的。

197
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:13,760
And there's also another meaning to this, right?
而且这个词还有另一个意思，对吧？

198
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:14,760
Apart from understand.
除了理解之外。

199
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:15,760
Yeah.
是的。

200
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:16,960
It can also mean I like it.
它也可以表示我喜欢。

201
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:17,960
Okay.
好的。

202
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:20,320
So I really dig this type of music.
所以我真的很喜欢这种音乐。

203
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:22,280
Or I really dig this restaurant.
或者我真的很喜欢这家餐厅。

204
00:07:22,280 --> 00:07:23,280
Okay.
好的。

205
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:24,880
So it's kind of, I like it.
所以这有点像，我喜欢它。

206
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:26,240
All right.
好的。

207
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:30,440
Now moving on, he said we could throw a bash here.
现在继续，他说我们可以在这里办个派对。

208
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:31,440
All right.
好的。

209
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:32,760
Throw a bash.
办个派对。

210
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:34,080
To throw a bash.
办个派对。

211
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:35,720
So first of all, what is a bash?
那么首先，什么是“bash”？

212
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:37,040
A bash is a party.
“Bash”就是派对。

213
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:38,200
A really great party.
一个很棒的派对。

214
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:39,560
An amazing party.
一个超棒的派对。

215
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:43,720
Now I want to look at this verb to throw something.
现在我想看看“throw something”这个动词。

216
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:46,680
So we know that you throw a ball, right?
我们知道你可以扔一个球，对吧？

217
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:47,680
Right.
对。

218
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:48,960
But how can you throw a party?
但你怎么能“扔”一个派对呢？

219
00:07:48,960 --> 00:07:53,280
Well, it's basically saying you organize or you host a party.
嗯，基本上就是说你组织或举办一个派对。

220
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:54,280
Okay.
好的。

221
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:55,680
And how can you use this phrase?
那你怎么用这个短语呢？

222
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:56,680
Okay.
好的。

223
00:07:56,680 --> 00:08:01,760
So I can say, last week I threw a birthday party in my house.
所以我可以这样说，上周我在家办了一个生日派对。

224
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:02,760
Okay.
好的。

225
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:06,520
Or let's throw a bash to celebrate your engagement.
或者咱们办个派对庆祝你订婚。

226
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:07,520
Okay.
好的。

227
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:11,960
Or next week I'm going to throw a dinner party at my house.
或者下周我要在家办个晚宴派对。

228
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:12,960
Okay.
好的。

229
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:13,960
So to throw a party.
所以就是“办个派对”。

230
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:17,120
And it's usually used for parties, right?
而且它通常用于派对，对吧？

231
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:18,120
Right.
对。

232
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:19,120
You wouldn't throw a...
你不会说办个……

233
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:20,120
Throw a meeting.
办个会议。

234
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:21,120
All right.
好的。

235
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:22,120
No.
不会。

236
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:23,120
Okay.
好的。

237
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:26,360
