这在现代英语中非常常见，我觉得我们需要一些例子。

242
00:08:35,920 --> 00:08:38,160
Example one.
例子一。

243
00:08:38,160 --> 00:08:42,040
Hey man, watch where you're going.
嘿，老兄，看路。

244
00:08:42,040 --> 00:08:43,040
Example two.
例子二。

245
00:08:43,040 --> 00:08:46,960
Yeah, man, that's a great idea.
是啊，老兄，那是个好主意。

246
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:48,360
Example three.
例子三。

247
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:52,760
Man, that was awesome.
老兄，那太棒了。

248
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:57,200
So man is one of those words that you just use at the end of your sentences.
所以“man”是那种你放在句子末尾用的词。

249
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,200
Or the beginning.
或者开头。

250
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,200
Or the beginning.
或者开头。

251
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,200
Anywhere.
任何地方。

252
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:02,160
And so you say, hey man, or yeah man.
所以你可以说，嘿，老兄，或者是啊，老兄。

253
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:03,160
Yeah.
是的。

254
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:06,440
What about, do you have to be a man to use it?
那是不是必须得是男人才能用这个词？

255
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:08,760
Or do you have to be talking to a man to use it?
或者你必须跟男人说话才能用？

256
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:10,120
No, not really.
不，不一定。

257
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:12,600
Men and women use the word man.
男人和女人都用“man”这个词。

258
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:15,800
And you can call a girl like, hey man, how are you?
你也可以对一个女孩说，嘿，老兄，你好吗？

259
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:16,800
Yeah.
是的。

260
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:19,960
But that sort of means that she's a really, really good friend.
但这意味着她是非常非常好的朋友。

261
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:22,880
Like the same level of friend as your guy friends.
就像和你男性朋友一样的亲密程度。

262
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:23,880
Yeah.
是的。

263
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:24,880
Yeah.
是的。

264
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:25,880
Exactly.
没错。

265
00:09:25,880 --> 00:09:26,880
Okay.
好的。

266
00:09:26,880 --> 00:09:27,880
Very good.
非常好。

267
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:30,040
